  <description><![CDATA[<p>Torbole is a compact bustling lakeside resort surrounded by a hilly back drop, very typical of the Northern region of the lake. With an excellent position for water sports, beach-life as well as cycling, it is a good all-round resort for an active as well as a relaxing holiday. The long promenade extends all the way to Riva which is 4km away, and is perfect for cycling or strolling. Torbole’s lively and informal café culture which sits alongside relaxing restaurants and ice cream bars, is known throughout Lake Garda. Nago, close by, is a small attractive mountain village above Torbole, which gives easy access to great walking trails and spectacular views. The midday breeze is perfect for cooling off in the balmy summer temperatures and filling the sails of the windsurfers. A great place to use as a base for exploring the lake and enjoying some active as well as leisurely days.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
